article.headline: Montana 63, Denver 44
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Kyle Sharp and Anthony Johnson came off the bench to score 13 points apiece in Montana's 63-44 win over Denver on Thursday night. Denver kept the game close during the first half, going into the break down only 27-26. But Montana (4-4) went on 20-3 run early in the second half to go ahead 47-32. Johnson and Jordan Hasquet scored five points apiece in the run, and the Grizzlies missed only three shots from the floor in the second half. Nate Rohnert led the Pioneers (0-5) with 14 points, and Rob Lewis added 12. Rohnert scored all but one of his points in the first half. The Grizzlies hit 63 percent from the field, compared to 40.5 percent shooting by Denver.
